.TH ASENSE-CONFIGURE-USER 8 "19 July 2026" "ASense 0.2.1" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
asense-configure-user \- select the desktop account allowed to control ASense
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B asense-configure-user
.I USER
.br
.B asense-configure-user --auto
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B asense-configure-user
creates the private, socket-activated ASense control endpoint for one local
non-root desktop account.  It must be run as root.
.PP
The
.B --auto
form preserves a valid existing selection.  Otherwise it selects an account
only when exactly one active local desktop session, or exactly one regular
home-directory account, can be identified.  Ambiguous selection fails without
opening the control socket.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/asense/desktop-user
Persisted selected account.
.TP
.I /etc/systemd/system/asense.socket
Generated systemd socket unit with restrictive ownership and mode.
.TP
.I /usr/libexec/asense/asense.socket.in
Packaged socket-unit template.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR asense (1),
.BR systemd.socket (5)
